The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, October 25, 2004

 Roads to avoid

 Immersion processions to take the following thoroughfares to the ghats:

 N Banerjee Road, SP Mukherjee Road, Beadon Street, Aurobindo Sarani and Rashbehari Avenue. Police contingents will be deployed along the routes from 4 pm. Normal traffic will be diverted as and when required.

 Exhibition

 Pressed bamboo craft and lacquerware from Vietnam on view at 16 Hindustan Park, 10 am to 8 pm.

 Russia at the United Nations Organisation, an exhibition of books and photographs to commemorate the World Day of the UN, at Gorky Sadan.

 Theatre

 Gandhar will stage Char Duar, directed by Meghnad Bhattacharjee, at Academy of Fine Arts, 6.30 pm.

 Workshop

 Dona Ganguly will conduct an Odissi dance workshop at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, 10 am onwards.

 Art watch

 Durga 2004, an exhibition of paintings and drawings at Galerie La Mere, Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, 4 pm to 8 pm.

 Paintings by eminent artists of Bengal on display at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3 pm to 8 pm.




